<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Trucker Charged in Amtrak Collision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAGLE LAKE, Texas (AP) -- The truck driver who is blamed for the  
crash of an Amtrak train that injured several people was charged 
Monday with failing to stop for the train. 
</P>
<P>
	David Bubela faces a maximum fine $200 if convicted of the  
misdemeanor. 
</P>
<P>
	Bubela, 21, told officials he did not see a stop sign posted in  
front of the rural crossing Thursday when the Orlando, Fla.-bound 
Sunset Limited slammed into his truck. 
</P>
<P>
	The impact derailed 13 cars and left 21 people injured.  
</P>
<P>
	Bubela will not be charged in connection with the tanker truck's  
faulty brakes or missing log book, violations that apparently 
played no role in the accident, said Tom Vinger, a spokesman for 
the state Department of Public Safety. 
</P>
</TEXT>
