<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Prestigious Law Firms To Merge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The partners of two prestigious U.S. and British  
law firms have approved a merger and have plans to add a third, 
German, partner to the union. 
</P>
<P>
	The combination of New York-based Rogers &AMP; Wells and Britain's  
Clifford Chance, the first marriage of major U.S. and British law 
firms, was approved overwhelmingly by the firms' partners over the 
weekend, Rogers &AMP; Wells said in a statement issued yesterday. 
</P>
<P>
	They also announced an agreement in principle to merge with a  
leading German law firm, Punder, Volhard, Wever and Axster. 
</P>
<P>
	The partners of all three firms are to vote in September on the  
three-way combination, which will take effect Jan. 1, 2000, will 
result in one of the world's largest law firms with 2,700 lawyers 
and 30 offices worldwide, the statement said. 
</P>
<P>
	``We will succeed because all three firms share a strong  
commitment to developing a single, integrated culture, drawing on 
the best of each, that is dedicated to excellence in client 
service, teamwork and training,'' said Larry Cranch, managing 
partner at Rogers &AMP; Wells. 
</P>
<P>
	The combined firm will be known as Clifford Chance Rogers &AMP;  
Wells in the United States, Clifford Chance in England and Clifford 
Chance Punder in Germany and other European countries, Rogers &AMP; 
Wells said. 
</P>
<P>
	The mergers are expected to spark similar unions between firms  
amid a trend of consolidation in the increasingly international 
field of law. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
