<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Canseco Out Six Weeks After Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Jose Canseco is expected to make a full recovery  
from back surgery and could be back on the field for the Tampa Bay 
Devil Rays within six weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	The slugger, who leads the AL with 31 homers, underwent a  
90-minute operation Sunday to repair a herniated disc. Doctors said 
he will not be able to resume baseball workouts for at least a 
month. 
</P>
<P>
	The AL announced Baltimore's Harold Baines will replace Canseco  
in Tuesday night's All-Star game. 
</P>
<P>
	The 35-year-old designated hitter, elected to the All-Star team  
for the first time in seven years, has been hampered by back 
trouble much of his career. He had surgery for a ruptured disc on 
his left side in 1996, but had remained healthy enough this year to 
play in 82 of Tampa Bay's first 86 games. 
</P>
<P>
	Dr. Tom Tolli and Dr. Gary Giesseke removed two fragments from  
Canseco's lower right back Sunday in Miami. 
</P>
<P>
	``We expect a full recovery,'' Tolli following the Devil Rays'  
3-2 loss to the Florida Marlins. ``Jose had the option of 
non-surgical care but the amount of pain he was in was the deciding 
factor. He wanted it done as soon as possible.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Canseco left Friday's game against the Marlins in the eighth  
inning with intense back pain. He had an MRI that revealed a 
severely compressed nerve was causing weakness in the toes of his 
right foot. 
</P>
<P>
	It was unclear when or how Canseco, a six-time All-Star, did  
something to cause the pain to flare. 
</P>
<P>
	``I talked to him and he can't pinpoint anything,'' manager  
Larry Rothschild said. 
</P>
<P>
	``He said it came on a little bit. He took one swing Friday he  
thinks might have had some effect on him but he really didn't know. 
He slid into third on the one play when he got thrown out, but 
really couldn't pinpoint anything. He felt more that it was just 
coming on over time and it got aggravated enough and that was it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Canseco also missed the All-Star game because of injuries in  
1989 and 1992. 
</P>
<P>
	``We've had a lot of injuries this season, but obviously this is  
a big one,'' Rothschild said. ``There's nothing we can do about 
it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Canseco, who turned 35 on July 2, missed 12 games in June and  
July last year with similar back spasms but didn't miss a start 
following the All-Star break. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was a big surprise,'' Devil Rays closer Roberto Hernandez  
said. ``He's in the starting lineup on the first day (of the 
series), and the second day he's not here. On the third day, he's 
getting operated on. He's a tough guy to replace.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Canseco, who has 428 career homers, had two stints on the DL due  
to back ailments in 1997. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
