<HEADLINE> 'American Pie' Leads Box Office / Box Office  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Will Smith's critically brutalized ``Wild  
Wild West'' now has ``American Pie'' in its face. 
</P>
<P>
	The gross-out comedy knocked the sci-fi western out of the No. 1  
spot at the weekend box office with $18.7 million in ticket sales. 
</P>
<P>
	``Wild Wild West'' lost nearly 40 percent of its audience in its  
second week, earning $16.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The terrorism thriller ``Arlington Road,'' the week's only other  
new film in wide release, opened in sixth place with $7.5 million. 
</P>
