<HEADLINE> Prodigy, uBid Team for Web Auctions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WHITE PLAINS, N.Y. (AP) -- Prodigy today announced that it and  
the auction Web site uBid will partner to give Prodigy members 
one-click access to bid on and buy items over the Web. 
</P>
<P>
	The agreement will give Prodigy members access to all of uBid's  
auction categories directly from their individual Prodigy 
homepages. 
</P>
<P>
	uBid, which will begin the service with Prodigy later this  
month, is a direct business-to-consumer site. Once an item is bid 
on and won, the consumer pays uBid directly, which then ships the 
product. 
</P>
<P>
	Also today, the Internet search and directory service Lycos  
launched an auction service that will match online buyers with both 
individual and retail sellers. 
</P>
<P>
	Lycos Auction and Tripod Auctions will let both buyers and  
sellers link to the sites. This will allow Lycos members not only 
to buy items from their personal start pages, but also to put items 
up for auction as well. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
