<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Mixed; Dow Up 10.44 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were narrowly mixed in early trading  
today as investors awaited the flood of second-quarter earnings 
reports expected over the next two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	At 10 a.m. on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was  
up 10.44 at 11,204.14, taking the blue chips further into record 
territory. The Dow had a new closing high Friday of 11,193.70. 
</P>
<P>
	Broader stock indicators were mixed. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500  
index was off 1.16 at 1,402.12 and the Nasdaq composite index rose 
0.45 to 2,783.52. 
</P>
<P>
	With quarterly profit reports beginning in earnest this week,  
traders were hesitant to make any big bets. Most stocks traded in a 
narrow range in the early going. 
</P>
<P>
	Computer stocks were among those making big moves. Gateway rose  
1 3/16 to 68 13/16 and Sun Microsystems rose 1 1/16 to 74. 
</P>
<P>
	But Internet stocks were lower. Yahoo! was off 4 1/4 at 155 3/4, and  
Infoseek was down 4 5/16 at 47 3/16. 
</P>
<P>
	Advancing and declining issues were about even on the New York  
Stock Exchange, where volume came to 94.52 million shares, modestly 
ahead of Friday's pace. 
</P>
<P>
	The NYSE composite index was off 0.16 at 657.52, and the  
American Stock Exchange composite index was unchanged at 812.73. 
</P>
<P>
	Overseas, Japan's Nikkei stock average rose 1.88 percent. In  
afternoon trading, Germany's DAX index was up 0.63 percent, 
Britain's FT-SE 100 was up 0.77 percent, and France's CAC-40 was up 
0.82 percent. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
