<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Prairie View A&AMP;M Suspends Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas (AP) -- Prairie View A&AMP;M suspended football  
coach Greg Johnson while the school investigates alleged 
irregularities of an unspecified nature. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson was placed on administrative leave with pay last week  
after the university received an anonymous letter alleging 
irregularities in the football program, said Larry Raab, Prairie 
View's vice president of operations. 
</P>
<P>
	Clifton Gilliard, the school's assistant athletic director, was  
appointed interim coach. 
</P>
<P>
	Raab said the allegations have been reported to the Texas A&AMP;M  
University System and will be reported to the NCAA ``once 
appropriate information is gathered upon which we can base a 
report.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Raab declined to detail the nature of the allegations.  
</P>
<P>
	Prairie View snapped its NCAA-record 80-game losing streak with  
a 14-12 victory over Langston at Oklahoma City on Sept. 26. It 
ended a string of losses dating back to Oct. 28, 1989 when the team 
beat Mississippi Valley State 21-12. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
