<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Unity Gays Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- In a story Saturday about the National Lesbian  
and Gay Journalists Association proposing stronger ties with a 
minority journalists group, The Associated Press incorrectly quoted 
the president of Unity: Journalists of Color, Inc. 
</P>
<P>
	The statement by Catalina Camia, president of Unity: Journalists  
of Color, Inc., should have read: ``The Unity board will take up 
the proposal in the fall. We felt it was not fair to NLGJA to take 
up the issue in the middle of the Unity convention. We're all very 
busy.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The original story misquoted Camia as saying that Unity felt it  
was ``not fair of NLGJA to take up the issue'' during the 
convention. 
  	   	
