<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-12 07:20:23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rehnquist Solves Newspaper Riddle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The Washington Post's Dr. Gridlock column  
posed this riddle: What automobile is referred to in a license 
plate that reads 1 DIV 0? 
</P>
<P>
	The reader who figured it out was Chief Justice William H.  
Rehnquist. 
</P>
<P>
	``Dear Dr. Gridlock: ... I believe it refers to an Infiniti,  
since when you divide 0 into 1 the result is infinity,'' the 
nation's top-ranking judge wrote. 
</P>
<P>
	When Ron Shaffer, who writes the column, called Rehnquist's  
office at the Supreme Court to verify his entry and congratulate 
the winner, a delighted Janet Barnes, the chief justice's 
secretary, asked, ``Did he win?'' 
</P>
<P>
	Rehnquist's winning response was published today.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
