<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Rain dampened the Mid-Atlantic on Monday. The Southeast also saw  
storms, while much of the Northeast and Plains were fair and dry. 
</P>
<P>
	Rain extended from Maryland and Delaware, south into Tennessee  
and North Carolina. 
</P>
<P>
	Strong thunderstorms were seen from southern Georgia and  
northern Florida, west across southern Alabama, Louisiana and 
central Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	High pressure extending from the Northeast, west through the  
Great Lakes and Ohio Valley into the Plains brought fair and dry 
weather to most of the northern and central United States. 
</P>
<P>
	A few scattered showers and thundershowers remained over the  
Southwest. 
</P>
<P>
	Fair and dry weather persisted over the Pacific Northwest.  
</P>
<P>
	Temperatures across the Lower 48 ranged from a low of 38 in  
Leadville, Colo., to an afternoon-high of 95 in Yuma, Ariz., and El 
Centro, Calif. With the heat index, it felt like 102 in Yuma. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
