<P>
	Dow Closes at Record High 11,200.98  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow industrials edged to another record high  
today, but most stocks fell in cautious trading before the 
impending flood of quarterly profit reports. The Dow turned 
positive just before the end of trading, finishing 7.28 higher at 
11,200.98. It was the third record high close in four sessions for 
the Dow, which has now gained more than 2,000 points, or 22 
percent, in 1999. Broader stock indicators posted small losses, 
with the Nasdaq composite index pulling back over the final half 
hour to miss out on another record high. It fell 2.39 to 2,790.68. 

