<P>
	Disney Acquires Rest of Infoseek  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Walt Disney Co. is consolidating its online  
strategy by acquiring the rest of Infoseek Corp. that it doesn't 
already own. Disney will pool its existing Internet assets with 
those of Sunnyvale, Calif.-based Infoseek into the go.com site they 
currently operate, which will then serve as the online arm of the 
entertainment conglomerate. Disney had already taken a 42 percent 
stake in Infoseek last year and worked with it to create the Go 
Network, which is powered by Infoseek's search capabilities. 
Infoseek stock was down 3 5/8 at 47 7/8. Disney was up 1/4 at 27 4/8. 

</P>
<P>
	IBM Buys Sequent for $810 Million  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- IBM announced today it would pay $810 million  
for Sequent Computer Systems Inc., a struggling maker of powerful 
business computers, in a cash deal that aims to fill an important 
slot in IBM's product line. Sequent is a leading seller of high-end 
computers and software that use Intel Corp.'s microprocessor chips. 
IBM plans to use Sequent's specialized technology in networked 
machines it will pitch as an inexpensive substitute to traditional 
mainframes that handle the biggest computer jobs, such as tracking 
inventories or millions of bank transactions. IBM stock was up 
13/16 at 138 3/16. Sequent was down 11/64 at 17 17/64. 

</P>
