in Toronto-based Rogers Communications Inc. as part of an agreement 
to develop new digital television services to Canadian homes. The 
collaboration disclosed today will provide Canadian television 
viewers with interactive services, including Internet and e-mail, 
operating through advanced set-top boxes. As part of the agreement, 
Rogers is to license Microsoft software to support at least 1 
million set-top boxes. Microsoft shares were trading up 1 3/8 to 94 5/8. 

</P>
