grim. He noted weak levels of personal consumption and capital 
expenditures and an unemployment hovering around record highs. But 
Miyazawa also told Parliament that the 1.9 percent growth in the 
nation's economy in the first three months of the year shows that 
``some bright signs are beginning to be seen.'' 

