<P>
	Major Offshore Drilling Co. Coming  
</P>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- Schlumberger Ltd. will spin off its offshore  
drilling operations and combine them with Transocean Offshore Inc. 
to create the world's largest offshore drilling company. The new 
company will be called Transocean Sedco Forex and have about 7,500 
employees. Schlumberger stockholders will receive new shares valued 
at $3.2 billion as part of the agreement. Schlumberger stockholders 
will own 52 percent of the new company, receiving roughly one share 
of the new company for every five Schlumberger shares they own. 

