<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Eubanks Discusses 'Newlywed Game' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- For game show host Bob Eubanks, there's one  
moment on ``The Newlywed Game'' that will be hard to match. 
</P>
<P>
	In an interview in Monday's Los Angeles Times, Eubanks recalled  
asking a contestant to remember something her husband told her not 
to talk about. 
</P>
<P>
	``She answered that her husband and her cousin were going to  
kill her uncle for the insurance money,'' Eubanks said. ``I was 
shocked, but even more taken aback when the husband returned and 
matched the answer.'' 
</P>
<P>
	He didn't elaborate on whether the conversation was a joke or if  
there was any criminal investigation. 
</P>
<P>
	Eubanks has been a TV game show host since the mid-1960s.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
