<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Down 8.24; Nasdaq Down 12.78 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were mostly lower today as a cautious  
market awaited the flood of second-quarter earnings reports 
expected over the next two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	At 11 a.m. on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was  
down 8.24 at 11,185.46 after rising in early trading. 
</P>
<P>
	Broader stock indicators were also down. The Standard &AMP; Poor's  
500 index fell 6.77 to 1,396.51 and the Nasdaq composite index fell 
12.78 to 2,780.29. 
</P>
<P>
	With quarterly profit reports beginning in earnest this week,  
traders were hesitant to make any big bets. Most stocks traded in a 
narrow range. 
</P>
<P>
	High-tech stocks gave up early gains. Intel, scheduled to  
release its earnings on Tuesday, was off 11/16 at 65 9/16. IBM 
dropped 1 1/2 to 135 7/8. 
</P>
<P>
	But Dell Computer, which got a vote of confidence from Goldman  
Sachs last week, was up 3/4 at 43 9/16. 
</P>
<P>
	Sevearl big Internet stocks were sharply lower. Yahoo! was off 6  
15/16 at 153 1/16, and Infoseek was down 4 1/2 at 47. 
</P>
<P>
	Declining issues were ahead of advancers by a margin of about 7  
to 6 on the New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 214.36 
million shares, slower than Friday's pace. 
</P>
<P>
	The NYSE composite index was off 1.68 at 656.00, and the  
American Stock Exchange composite index was up 1.06 at 813.79. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
