<HEADLINE> Yankees' Spencer To Start Rehab </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- New York Yankees outfielder Shane Spencer has  
been cleared to begin a rehabilitation program one week after being 
diagnosed for an irregular heartbeat. 
</P>
<P>
	Spencer, who was reevaluated Monday at Columbia Presbyterian  
Hospital, is in stable condition and his heartbeat is normal, 
according to the Yankees. 
</P>
<P>
