<HEADLINE> Brit Insurance Co. To Buy Orion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Royal &AMP; SunAlliance Insurance Group PLC has agreed  
to buy the U.S. insurance company Orion Capital Corp. for $1.4 
billion. 
</P>
<P>
	The deal announced Monday would give Orion shareholders $50 a  
share, a 23 percent premium over its Friday closing share price and 
a 65 percent premium from the share price a month ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Orion shares soared 16, or by $6.56 1/4, to close at $47.31 1/4 a  
share on the New York Stock Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
	Both boards have approved the transaction, Royal &AMP; SunAlliance  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	The British insurance company operates in more than 55 nations,  
and is currently among the top 30 insurers in the United States, 
the company said. 
</P>
<P>
	``This transaction effectively doubles the size of Royal &AMP;  
SunAlliance U.S.A.,'' said Group Chief Executive Bob Mendelsohn. 
His company had 3,500 employees in the United States and Orion, 
based in Farmington, Conn., currently employs 3,900. 
  	   	
</P>
