<HEADLINE> NCAA Picks Basketball Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OVERLAND PARK, Kan. (AP) -- Mountain West Conference Commissioner  
Craig Thompson will become chairman of the NCAA Division I Men's 
Basketball Committee effective Sept. 1. 
</P>
<P>
	He succeeds University of Kentucky Athletic Director C. M.  
Newton, whose term on the committee will end. 
</P>
<P>
	Thompson will serve for one year and be succeeded as chairman by  
Big East Conference Commissioner Mike Tranghese. 
</P>
<P>
	Thompson is a former commissioner of the Sun Belt and American  
South Conferences, and last year he was named the first 
commissioner of the Mountain West, which officially became an NCAA 
member this month. He has been a member of the basketball committee 
since 1995. 
</P>
<P>
	Tranghese, Big East commissioner since 1990, has served on the  
basketball committee since 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointments to the committee chairmanship were made by the  
NCAA Championships/Competition Cabinet and announced Monday. 
  	   	
</P>
