<HEADLINE> ESPN To Replay World Cup Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The United States World Cup victory over China  
on Saturday will be replayed Tuesday night opposite the Major 
League Baseball All-Star game. 
</P>
<P>
	ESPN will re-broadcast the game Tuesday at 8 p.m, the same time  
that Fox begins its All-Star game telecast at Fenway Park in 
Boston. 
</P>
<P>
	The shootout victory by the United States was the most-watched  
soccer game ever on U.S. network television, with a 13.3 overnight 
rating and a 32 share on ABC. The network said that an estimated 40 
million viewers watched. 
</P>
<P>
