<HEADLINE> Rapper DMX Fined $25 for Obscenities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PORT-OF-SPAIN, Trinidad (AP) -- After spending two nights in  
jail, U.S. rapper DMX was released Monday when he paid a $25 fine 
for using obscene language at a local concert. 
</P>
<P>
	Magistrate Deborah Thomas Felix gave the musician, whose real  
name is Earl Simmons, the option of the fine or a month's 
imprisonment at hard labor. 
</P>
<P>
	He had pleaded guilty to the obscenity charge stemming from his  
Saturday night concert. 
</P>
<P>
	As police escorted Simmons off the stage, they fired shots in  
the air to disperse unruly fans who were protesting the singer's 
removal. 
</P>
<P>
	At the hearing, the rapper thanked police who handled his  
arrest, saying the situation could have become violent. He also 
apologized to the Caribbean country, saying he was ignorant of its 
laws. 
</P>
<P>
	The Trinidad Guardian newspaper Monday quoted concert promoters  
as saying he might not get paid because he broke a contract in 
which he had agreed not to use any obscene language. 
  	   	
</P>
