<HEADLINE> Punch Still Wants Allied Domecq Pubs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Punch Taverns Ltd. plans to make a final,  
irrevocable offer this week for 3,600 pubs it hopes to buy from 
Allied Domecq PLC, a Punch spokesman said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Punch has twice sweetened its initial offer in a bidding war  
with rival Whitbread PLC, and it criticized Allied's decision last 
week to recommend that shareholders approve Whitbread's smaller 
bid. 
</P>
<P>
	Punch will issue its final offer by Wednesday, the spokesman  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Punch has offered $4.53 billion in cash together with an option  
for shares in Bass PLC. Whitbread has offered $4.42 billion in cash 
and stock. 
</P>
<P>
	Allied's management explained its preference for Whitbread by  
saying it believed the Whitbread offer would allow for a speedier 
sale of its pubs. 
</P>
<P>
	Allied wants to sell its pubs to focus on its other businesses,  
including some of the world's best-known liquor brands -- like 
Beefeater gin and Canadian Club whiskey -- along with the Dunkin' 
Donut and Baskin-Robbins ice cream chains. 
  	   	
</P>
