<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 28 in Early Trading / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 28 points  
in today's early going. Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange 
hold an 8-7 lead over decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up 13 points and the S&AMP;P 500 Index  
is up three points. 
</P>
<P>
	Wall Streeters will be focusing on the bottom line as  
second-quarter profit reporting gets under way in earnest this 
week. 
</P>
<P>
	Five components of the Dow Jones industrial average will report  
this week. And nearly every sector of the market will represented 
-- from high-tech heavyweight Intel to biotech leader Amgen and 
brokerage bigwig Merrill Lynch. Not to be left out are such 
consumer stalwarts as Gillette and Coca-Cola. 

  	   	
</P>
