<HEADLINE> Rob Tallas Re-Signed by Bruins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- The Boston Bruins re-signed goaltender Rob Tallas  
to a one-year contract, the team announced Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms were not disclosed.  
</P>
<P>
	Tallas, 26, was 7-7-2 with 2.61 goals-against-average in 17  
games last season as Byron Dafoe's backup. 
</P>
<P>
	Tallas came to the Bruins in 1994 on a tryout basis at training  
camp. Signed by the team as a free agent in 1995, he split his next 
three seasons between Boston and its American Hockey League 
affiliate in Providence, R.I. 
</P>
<P>
	Tallas has a career record of 22-22-6 and a 2.71  
goals-against-average. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's proven to be a solid goaltender in this league and has  
performed well in his role for the Bruins over the past several 
seasons,'' Bruins vice president of operations Mike O'Connell said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
