<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are moving substantially or trading  
heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	
</P>
<P>
	Red Roof Inns, up 4 1/8 at 22 7/16  
</P>
<P>
	Accor, the European company that controls the Motel 6 chain,  
offered to buy Red Roof for $673 million, or $22.75 per share, and 
about $500 million in assumed debt. Accor said it has a commitment 
from the Morgan Stanley Real Estate Fund and other investors who 
together own 68.3 percent of Red Roof, based in Columbus, Ohio. 

</P>
<P>
	Orion Capital, up 6 9/16 at 47 5/15  
</P>
<P>
	Royal &AMP; SunAlliance Insurance Group has acquired Orion Capital,  
a U.S. insurance company, for $1.4 billion, or $50 a share. Royal &AMP; 
SunAlliance operates in more than 55 nations, and is currently 
among the top 30 insurers in the United States. 

</P>
<P>
	World Color Press, up 5 1/16 at 34 7/8  
</P>
<P>
	Quebecor Printing will acquire World Color Press for about $1.4  
billion, or $36 a share, in cash and stock in a deal that will 
create the largest commercial printer in the world. Montreal-based 
Quebecor is also assuming $1.3 billion in debt from World Color, 
which is based in Greenwich, Conn. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	
</P>
<P>
	Specialty Care Network, up 15/16 at 5  
</P>
<P>
	The company's HealthGrades.com unit will provide health care  
ratings information for the Better Health and Parent Soup channels 
of the iVillage.com women's network. HealthGrades.com also will be 
promoted throughout iVillage.com and in weekly iVillage.com 
newsletters. Specialty Care is based in Lakewood, Colo. 

</P>
<P>
	Central Garden &AMP; Pet, down 1 13/16 at 8 1/2  
</P>
<P>
	Scotts Co. plans to begin direct sales of its Ortho, Roundup and  
Miracle-Gro gardening products to certain retailers, altering an 
exclusive distribution pact between the companies. Central Garden, 
based in Lafayette, Calif., said the business likely to be taken 
over by Scotts will have sales of up to $250 million and gross 
profits of up to $25 million this year. 

</P>
<P>
	Caere, down 2 5/8 at 11 1/8  
</P>
<P>
	The scanner software maker warned it will report disappointing  
profits for the second quarter. Caere, based in Los Gatos, Calif., 
said weak hardware revenue and weaker-than-expected software sales 
in Europe led to the shortfall. 

  	   	
</P>
