<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar At New High Vs. Euro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar hit a new high against the euro today  
and gained against most other currencies in European trading. Gold 
prices fell. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0139, below the record low close of  
$1.0168 on Thursday, and down from $1.0210 Friday. Later, in early 
afternoon trading in New York, the euro traded at $1.0136. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Friday,  
included 122.21 Japanese yen, down from 122.28;1.5844 Swiss francs, 
up from 1.5725; 1.4802 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4700. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.5530, up from $1.5515.  
</P>
<P>
	In early afternoon trading in New York, the dollar bought 122.20  
yen, and the pound was worth $1.5553. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth 1.9290 German marks, up from 1.9156; 
6.4696 French francs, up from 6.4247; 2.1735 Dutch guilders, up 
from 2.1584; and 1,909.72 Italian lire, up from 1,896.44 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $255.00 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$256.40 on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid price was $255.65, down from $256.25.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold fell $1.80 in Hong Kong to $256.15.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.21 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$5.18. 
</P>
